Most of the code consists of small functions such as<p><pre><code>    let load_prog_platter a = !platters.(0) <- a; a
</code></pre>
for which comments would just get in the way. I don't know if you know OCaml, but that's roughly the same as<p><pre><code>    plat load_prog_platter(plat a) {
        (*platters)[0] = a;
        return a;
    }
</code></pre>
I don't think commenting that should be necessary.<p>He did comment one part, though: "(* we deliberately use Array.get to check bounds; use unsafe_ for speed *)".<p>(The only big function, exec, is an Opcode -> Action table.)
